{"session_id":"svc-1778823278172410593","seq":0,"type":"session.start","ts":"2026-05-15T05:34:39.061614896Z","data":{"provider":"","model":"gpt-5.4","sticky":{"key_present":true,"bonus":0},"utilization":{"observed_at":"0001-01-01T00:00:00Z"},"requested_harness":"codex","resolved_harness":"codex","harness_source":"request_harness","requested_model":"gpt-5.4","resolved_model":"gpt-5.4","work_dir":"/var/tmp/ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-fa6eedcc-20260515T053424-4c9c3bbc","max_iterations":0,"prompt":"\u003cexecute-bead\u003e\n  \u003cinstructions\u003e\nYou are executing one bead inside an isolated DDx execution worktree. The bead\u0026#39;s \u0026lt;description\u0026gt; and \u0026lt;acceptance\u0026gt; are the completion contract — every AC must be provably satisfied by a specific code, test, or file you can point to after your commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Step 0: size check\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Too big if any holds:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- More than ~6 ACs spanning unrelated subsystems.\u0026#xA;- AC mixes design, implementation, integration tests, and docs as separate deliverables.\u0026#xA;- Description names multiple feature-sized sub-pieces.\u0026#xA;- More than ~500 lines across ~5+ files in unrelated packages.\u0026#xA;- If the bead description exceeds 8000 bytes, treat Step 0 as a split-first pass.\u0026#xA;- Auto-decomposition is capped at depth 2: root beads may split once, decomposed children once more; third-level splits must be rejected with an explanation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If too big, decompose — do not attempt the work:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;1. `ddx bead create` for each child slice (copy parent\u0026#39;s labels and spec-id).\u0026#xA;2. `ddx bead dep add \u0026lt;child-id\u0026gt; \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt;` to record edges.\u0026#xA;3. `ddx bead update \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt; --notes \u0026#39;decomposed into \u0026lt;child-ids\u0026gt;\u0026#39;`.\u0026#xA;4. Write `.ddx/executions/20260515T053424-4c9c3bbc/no_changes_rationale.txt` listing child IDs, then stop.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;A clean decomposition is a success. Do not mix implementation with decomposition.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## How to work\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Read first. If the bead names files, specs, or prior beads, read them before editing — do not guess.\u0026#xA;- Cross-reference each AC against concrete evidence (test name, file path, function) before committing. If you cannot point at it, it is not done.\u0026#xA;- Run the project\u0026#39;s test and lint commands before committing. **Do not commit red code** — fix failures first.\u0026#xA;- Stage with `git add \u0026lt;specific-paths\u0026gt;`; never `git add -A` (the worktree may have unrelated WIP).\u0026#xA;- Commit exactly once when green; conventional-commit subject ending with `[\u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;]`. Stop after the commit.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s scope.\u0026#xA;- If you cannot finish, write `.ddx/executions/20260515T053424-4c9c3bbc/no_changes_rationale.txt` (what is done, what blocks, what a follow-up needs) before exiting. No commit and no rationale ⇒ DDx records `no_evidence_produced`. A well-justified no_changes beats a bad commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## no_changes contract\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;`.ddx/executions/20260515T053424-4c9c3bbc/no_changes_rationale.txt` must contain one:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- `verification_command: \u0026lt;cmd\u0026gt;` — repo cwd; exit 0 closes, nonzero rejects.\u0026#xA;- `status: open` + `reason: \u0026lt;retryable\u0026gt;` — open, smart retry.\u0026#xA;- `status: proposed` + `reason: \u0026lt;operator needed\u0026gt;` — operator lane.\u0026#xA;- `status: blocked` + `reason: \u0026lt;external blocker\u0026gt;` — blocked lane.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;No pseudo-statuses. Bare rationales and `status: needs_investigation` reject.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;To request orchestrator decomposition, add `orchestrator_action: decompose` alongside `status: open`.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Reports\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Freestanding artifacts (investigation reports, findings docs) go under `.ddx/executions/20260515T053424-4c9c3bbc/` (the per-attempt evidence directory under `.ddx/executions/`). **Never write reports to `/tmp` or any path outside the repository** — out-of-repo paths are invisible to the post-merge reviewer and cause BLOCK on missing evidence. If the bead names a specific in-repo path, use it; else default to `.ddx/executions/20260515T053424-4c9c3bbc/\u0026lt;short-name\u0026gt;.md`. Stage and commit the report alongside code.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Mode and overrides\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;DDX_MODE=bead_execution: edit code/docs for bead AC. Only broad queue-steward default is overridden; tracker, merge-policy, verification, safety stay active. Bead description/AC override CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, and project defaults.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Review gate\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- The review is a gate, not an escape hatch — meet every AC in this pass.\u0026#xA;- Address every BLOCKING `\u0026lt;review-findings\u0026gt;` item; do not declare `no_changes` with blocking findings open.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Constraints\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Work only inside this execution worktree.\u0026#xA;- Keep `.ddx/executions/` intact — DDx uses it as execution evidence.\u0026#xA;- **Never run `ddx init`** — the workspace is initialized; running it corrupts the bead queue.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s named scope.\u0026#xA;- Do not rewrite CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, or other project-instructions files unless the bead asks.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## When the work is done\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;After the commit succeeds and every AC is verified, stop. Return control to the orchestrator — do not keep exploring or testing.\n  \u003c/instructions\u003e\n  \u003cbead id=\"ddx-fa6eedcc\"\u003e\n    \u003ctitle\u003eddx home: presence-based root resolution + per-project worktree registry: part 2\u003c/title\u003e\n    \u003cdescription\u003e\nPROBLEM\u0026#xA;Parent bead ddx-06cbaa90 is too broad for one execution pass. This child owns part 2 of 5 of that parent scope.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;ROOT CAUSE\u0026#xA;PROBLEM (Principle 1 of epic ddx-602ae31a)\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Eliminate hardcoded .ddx/ paths so that DDx state anchors correctly regardless of whether the project has a .ddx/ folder. Today every code path joins filepath.Join(projectRoot, \u0026#34;.ddx\u0026#34;, ...) directly, so introducing an XDG fallback or any other root strategy means a many-callsite rewrite.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;DESIGN\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;ddxroot.Path(ctx, projectRoot) is the single accessor. It returns:\u0026#xA;- \u0026lt;projectRoot\u0026gt;/.ddx — when that directory exists (in-tree mode)\u0026#xA;- ${XDG_DATA_HOME}/ddx/projects/\u0026lt;host\u0026gt;/\u0026lt;owner\u0026gt;/\u0026lt;repo\u0026gt;/ — otherwise (convention mode)\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Project identity in convention mode is parsed from `git remote get-url origin`:\u0026#xA;- https://github.com/easel/ddx.git → github.com/easel/ddx\u0026#xA;- git@github.com:easel/ddx.git → github.com/easel/ddx\u0026#xA;- https://gitlab.example.com/team/repo → gitlab.example.com/team/repo\u0026#xA;- Local (no remote) → local/\u0026lt;basename\u0026gt;-\u0026lt;short-hash-of-abs-path\u0026gt;\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The XDG project directory IS a git repository — `git init`ed on first bootstrap. All DDx state for that project (beads.jsonl, attachments, archive, plugins, etc.) lives there and is versioned. Operators can `git remote add` it to a server to share state with teammates.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;WORKTREE REGISTRY (required, not speculative)\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Each XDG project root maintains \u0026lt;xdg\u0026gt;/worktrees.json:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;  {\u0026#34;paths\u0026#34;: [{\u0026#34;path\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;/Users/erik/Projects/ddx\u0026#34;, \u0026#34;first_seen_at\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;...\u0026#34;, \u0026#34;last_seen_at\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;...\u0026#34;, \u0026#34;hostname\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;...\u0026#34;}], \u0026#34;master\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;/Users/erik/Projects/ddx\u0026#34;}\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- The first worktree to bootstrap an XDG project is auto-marked master.\u0026#xA;- Subsequent worktrees register as non-master.\u0026#xA;- `ddx project worktree list` shows the registry.\u0026#xA;- `ddx project worktree master \u0026lt;path\u0026gt;` re-pins.\u0026#xA;- Audit log entries (bead events with result_rev/base_rev) include the master path so downstream tools resolve commit SHAs to a known worktree.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;DDX_ROOT NEVER PUNNED — bootstrap is atomic, idempotent, and a no-op when the directory already exists. Two concurrent ddx invocations on the same project must not race-create or race-write worktrees.json. Use file-locking (existing gitlock pattern from ddx-6a518fd9) where needed.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;AUDIT — every Go file in cli/ that contains the literal \u0026#34;.ddx\u0026#34; as a path segment must route through ddxroot.Path. Touched packages at minimum:\u0026#xA;- cli/cmd/ (every command that reads/writes state)\u0026#xA;- cli/internal/agent/ (execute_bead*, work/, escalation/)\u0026#xA;- cli/internal/bead/ (store, migrate, lifecycle)\u0026#xA;- cli/internal/serv\u0026#xA;...[truncated]\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;PROPOSED FIX\u0026#xA;Implement only this child acceptance slice:\u0026#xA;- TestDDxRoot_ConventionMode_XDGPath asserts Path returns ${XDG_DATA_HOME}/ddx/projects/github.com/easel/ddx for a project without .ddx/ and with `git remote get-url origin = git@github.com:easel/ddx.git`.\u0026#xA;- TestDDxRoot_ConventionMode_LocalFallback covers the no-remote `local/\u0026lt;basename\u0026gt;-\u0026lt;sha\u0026gt;/` form.\u0026#xA;- TestDDxRoot_URLParsing covers https, ssh, custom-host, missing-remote cases (table-driven).\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;NON-SCOPE\u0026#xA;Do not implement parent acceptance criteria assigned to sibling child beads. Preserve every parent non-scope constraint unless this child explicitly narrows it.\n    \u003c/description\u003e\n    \u003cacceptance\u003e\n1. TestDDxRoot_ConventionMode_XDGPath asserts Path returns ${XDG_DATA_HOME}/ddx/projects/github.com/easel/ddx for a project without .ddx/ and with `git remote get-url origin = git@github.com:easel/ddx.git`.\u0026#xA;2. TestDDxRoot_ConventionMode_LocalFallback covers the no-remote `local/\u0026lt;basename\u0026gt;-\u0026lt;sha\u0026gt;/` form.\u0026#xA;3. TestDDxRoot_URLParsing covers https, ssh, custom-host, missing-remote cases (table-driven).\n    \u003c/acceptance\u003e\n    \u003clabels\u003earea:config, area:refactor, kind:refactor, phase:3, initiative:zero-footprint, principle:ddx-home, decomposed\u003c/labels\u003e\n    \u003cmetadata parent=\"ddx-06cbaa90\" base-rev=\"4f977e5df86017441fd38e99619051373520fe2b\" bundle=\".ddx/executions/20260515T053424-4c9c3bbc\"/\u003e\n  \u003c/bead\u003e\n  \u003cgoverning\u003e\n    \u003cnote\u003eNo governing references were pre-resolved. The bead description above is the primary contract. If it names files, specs, or prior beads, read those before editing. Ground decisions in what is already in the repository; do not guess.\u003c/note\u003e\n  \u003c/governing\u003e\n\u003c/execute-bead\u003e\n","metadata":{"DDX_MODE":"bead_execution","attempt_id":"20260515T053424-4c9c3bbc","base_rev":"4f977e5df86017441fd38e99619051373520fe2b","bead_id":"ddx-fa6eedcc","bundle_path":".ddx/executions/20260515T053424-4c9c3bbc","correlation_id":"ddx-fa6eedcc:20260515T053424-4c9c3bbc","prompt_file":".ddx/executions/20260515T053424-4c9c3bbc/prompt.md","prompt_sha":"b33fa278a566c4f03c220c3fb977cf8a70c82a2d4c27a0cc038f6e53a9c73615","role":"implementer","session_id":"eb-a27b971a","worker_id":""}}}
